AN ACT relating to agriculture; directing the Council on Food
Security to conduct a study during the 2025-2026 interim
to evaluate food insecurity in this State and develop
strategies to coordinate statewide efforts to address food
insecurity; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Director of the State Department of Agriculture to
2 establish certain programs relating to the supply of food in this State, including the
3 Supplemental Food Program and the Home Feeds Nevada Agriculture Food
4 Purchase Program. (NRS 561.495, 561.515) Existing law further sets forth various
5 provisions to encourage the development of community gardens and urban farms in
6 this State which: (1) require certain entities, including the Council on Food Security
7 within the Department of Health and Human Services, to promote or encourage
8 such development; (2) authorize certain entities to use or lease certain land for the
9 purpose of community gardening or urban farming; and (3) authorize a partial
10 abatement of certain taxes for a parcel on which a community garden or urban farm
11 is located. (NRS 232.4966, 232.4968, 244.291, 244.339, 268.0191, 408.507,
12 528.135)
13 This bill directs the Council to conduct a study to evaluate food insecurity in
14 this State and develop strategies to coordinate statewide efforts to address food
15 insecurity which must include, without limitation: (1) an evaluation of the existing
16 laws and policies in this State that are designed to address food insecurity; (2) the
17 identification of areas in this State where community gardens or urban farms could
18 be developed to reduce levels of food insecurity; (3) a study of the coordination of
19 the efforts of certain entities to reduce food insecurity; and (4) recommendations
20 for strategies to reduce food insecurity through the coordination of the efforts of
